# Environment Variables for Lets-Dress
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (SQLite):
# No DATABASE_URL needed. SQLite file is created automatically at server/database.sqlite
# Just run: npm run dev
#
# CLOUD DEPLOYMENT (PostgreSQL on Railway):
# Set the variables below in Railway's Variables tab.

# ── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set this to your PostgreSQL connection string for cloud mode.
# Leave unset (or delete this line) to use local SQLite.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/dbname

# ── Server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to 'production' on Railway. Leave unset for local dev.
# NODE_ENV=production

# Railway sets PORT automatically — do not set it manually on Railway.
# PORT=3000
